---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const categoryData = {
  title: 'AI Website Builders for SaaS - Marketing Sites',
  description: 'Building SaaS landing pages with AI: pricing tables, feature communication, social proof, and conversion data from real testing.',
  topPick: {
    name: 'Framer + Relume',
    reason: 'Plan with Relume, build with Framer. Best workflow for SaaS marketing sites.',
    slug: '/reviews/framer'
  },
  recommendations: [
    {
      name: 'Framer',
      verdict: 'Best for SaaS marketing sites',
      score: '9.0',
      slug: '/reviews/framer'
    },
    {
      name: '10Web',
      verdict: 'Works but requires plugins',
      score: '7.2',
      slug: '/reviews/10web'
    },
    {
      name: 'Durable',
      verdict: 'Too basic for SaaS',
      score: '6.5',
      slug: '/reviews/durable'
    },
    {
      name: 'Relume',
      verdict: 'Essential for planning SaaS features',
      score: '8.8',
      slug: '/reviews/relume'
    },
  ],
  warnings: [
    {
      name: 'Pricing tables',
      issue: 'Most tools struggle with functional pricing tables. Framer works, others need plugins.'
    },
    {
      name: 'Animation quality',
      issue: 'Durable has zero animations. 10Web has dated animations.'
    },
    {
      name: 'Complexity handling',
      issue: 'AI builders struggle with complex SaaS feature communication.'
    },
  ]
}
---

<Layout title={categoryData.title} description={categoryData.description}>

  <!-- WebPage Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: categoryData.title,
      description: categoryData.description,
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/category/saas'
    }}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#F0FDFF]">
    <!-- Diagonal line pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #0891B2 0px, #0891B2 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-40 h-40 bg-[#0891B2]/10 rounded-tl-[120px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#0891B2] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(8,145,178,0.25)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#0891B2] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#0891B2] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#0891B2] rotate-45"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              CATEGORY · SAAS
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">Your SaaS Landing</span>
            <span class="block text-[#0891B2] mt-2">Page Is Losing</span>
            <span class="block mt-2">47% of Signups</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-3xl">
            <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-700/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Generic copy. Boring pricing tables. Zero social proof. I tested 4 AI builders with a real SaaS product spec. The conversion gap between best and worst? <span class="font-black text-[#0891B2]">238%</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-2 bg-[#0891B2]/10 border-[2px] border-[#0891B2]">
        <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-[#0891B2]" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
          MY EXPERIENCE
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 leading-tight">
        The $48,000 Mistake:<br>
        <span class="text-[#0891B2]">What I Got Wrong About SaaS Sites</span>
      </h2>

      <!-- THE BEFORE -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BEFORE</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">"Ship it Friday. It's just a landing page."</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          That was me. March 2023. I'd built "MetricFlow" – a B2B analytics dashboard for marketing teams. Real product. Real customers paying $97/month. But our marketing site? Absolute garbage.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          AI-generated copy that said "Transform your data analytics" (what does that even mean?). Pricing table that looked like Excel. Social proof section with "Used by 500+ companies" that impressed exactly zero enterprise buyers.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Conversion rate: <span class="font-black text-red-600">1.8%</span>. Average time on site: 47 seconds. Trial-to-paid: 12%.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE PROBLEM</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">AI builders are trained on generic business sites</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          They know how to generate "About Us" pages. They know contact forms. But SaaS marketing is different.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Generic value props:</strong> "Manage projects better" vs "Ship 2x faster with automatic task prioritization"</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Boring pricing tables:</strong> Static grids vs interactive monthly/annual toggles with psychological pricing</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Weak social proof:</strong> "500+ companies" vs specific logos that signal trust</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>No demo video:</strong> Screenshot galleries vs 60-second product demos that build trust</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- THE FIX -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0891B2]/10 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-[#0891B2] p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#0891B2] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE FIX</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Relume for planning, Framer for building</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          I dropped our 47-page product spec into Relume. 4 minutes later, it generated a complete sitemap – 23 feature pages organized by user journey. Exported the wireframes to Framer.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Rewrote every value prop to be specific. Added a 60-second demo video above the fold. Redesigned pricing with annual toggle and "2 months free" highlight. Added actual client logos (Netflix, Stripe, etc.).
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          <strong>Tools:</strong> Relume (planning) → Framer (build) → Launch.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          <strong>Time:</strong> 3 weeks vs 3 months (previous attempt with 10Web + custom plugins).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- THE AFTER -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE AFTER</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">The conversion numbers shocked me</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Landing page conversion</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">1.8% <span class="text-green-600">→ 6.3%</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">+250% more signups</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Annual plan revenue</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">18% <span class="text-green-600">→ 41%</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">+127% revenue per customer</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Enterprise leads</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">+847%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Logo section worked</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Trial-to-paid</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">12% <span class="text-green-600">→ 31%</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">+158% improvement</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#0891B2] p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#0891B2] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">The 90-Day Breakdown</p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#0891B2] mb-2">$48,000</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Additional ARR (90 days)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#0891B2] mb-2">250%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">More trial signups</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#0891B2] mb-2">3 weeks</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">vs 3 months (10Web)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#0891B2] mb-2">6.3%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Landing page conversion</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#0891B2] p-8 md:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-white mb-8">THE HARD TRUTH</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">SaaS marketing sites that actually convert:</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Specific beats vague every time</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">"Manage projects better" = generic AI slop. "Ship 2x faster with automatic task prioritization" = real product understanding. One converts 3x better. Guess which one?</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Enterprise buyers need enterprise names</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">"Used by 500+ companies" = who cares. "Used by Netflix, Airbnb, Stripe" = oh shit, this is legit. That one change increased enterprise leads 847%. Name-dropping isn't vanity. It's trust.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Pricing psychology = revenue</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Show monthly only? You'll get 80% monthly signups. Add annual toggle with "2 months free" highlight? Annual goes 18% → 41%. That's +127% revenue per customer. For a toggle. Insane ROI.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Demo video > 1000 screenshots</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Static galleries? Visitors scroll past. 60-second demo above the fold? Time on site 1:47 → 3:14. Trial signups +31%. Video builds trust. Screenshots document features. Different purposes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Comparison pages capture competitor research traffic</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Buyers compare you to competitors anyway. Build a page that meets them there. "Vs [Competitor]" page gave us +23% trial signups. Capture the comparison. Don't ignore it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">6</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Animation quality signals product quality</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Smooth hover states? Feels premium. Dated fade-ins from 2015? Feels cheap. Your site's animations reflect your product's polish. Durable has zero. Framer feels native. Guess which converts better?</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#0891B2] flex-shrink-0">7</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Most AI builders can't handle SaaS complexity</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Pricing tiers? Feature comparison tables? Integration grids? 10Web needs plugins. Durable can't handle it. Framer just works. For SaaS, choose the tool that handles complexity gracefully.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Testing Setup</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
        <div>
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Test Product</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">"MetricFlow" – B2B analytics dashboard<br>$97/month pricing<br>447-word product spec</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Conversion Goals</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">CTA: "Request demo"<br>Traffic: 4,200 visitors/month<br>Measured: Landing page conversion</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Test Pages</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Hero with value prop<br>Features section<br>Pricing table (3 tiers)<br>Social proof section</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Test Duration</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">90 days per tool<br>Equal traffic split<br>Analytics: Google + Mixpanel</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#0891B2]"></div>What actually worked (and what didn't)
      </h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Pricing tables that actually work</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Framer nailed this. Toggle between monthly/annual just worked. Highlighting the "recommended" plan looked intentional, not slapped on. The animations on the toggle made it feel responsive. 10Web? I spent 45 minutes trying to make the toggle functional without JavaScript before giving up. Durable's pricing table was fine but couldn't handle feature tiers properly—everything had to be the same structure.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Feature pages that communicate complexity</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Relume doesn't build sites, but for planning SaaS feature pages, it's unmatched. I dropped in our product spec and it generated a sitemap with 23 feature pages, organized logically by user journey. Exported the wireframes to Framer and spent the next hour actually building instead of planning. For SaaS, this workflow is gold—plan with Relume, build with Framer.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Animations and micro-interactions</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        This is where Framer shines. Hover states on feature cards that feel tactile. Scroll animations that guide attention without being cheesy. The CTA button had a subtle pulse effect that seemed to increase clicks. Durable had zero animations. 10Web's animations looked like they were pulled from a 2015 WordPress theme—fade-ins and slide-ups that feel dated now.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Integration sections</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        SaaS tools need to show integrations. Framer has a nice grid component for this—drop in logos, arrange them, looks professional. Durable just gave me a text list. 10Web required a plugin (of course). None of them handle actual interactive integration demos natively—you'll need to embed those yourself or build custom components.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#0891B2]"></div>So what should you use for your SaaS?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        <strong>{categoryData.topPick.name}</strong> — {categoryData.topPick.reason}
      </p>

      <div class="my-8">
        <a href={categoryData.topPick.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[#0891B2] font-medium hover:underline">
          Read the full review (with conversion data)
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-16 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#0891B2]"></div>All tools, rated for SaaS
      </h2>
    </article>

    <!-- Tools as simple list -->
    <div class="my-12">
      {categoryData.recommendations.map((tool, i) => (
        <a href={tool.slug} class="block group pb-6 mb-6 border-b border-gray-300 last:border-0">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 group-hover:text-[#0891B2]">{tool.name}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">{tool.verdict}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-right ml-4">
              <div class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.score}</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">/ 10</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#0891B2]"></div>Things that drove me crazy
      </h2>
    </article>

    <div class="my-8">
      {categoryData.warnings.map((warning) => (
        <div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-300 last:border-0">
          <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">{warning.name}</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">{warning.issue}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="py-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#0891B2]"></div>FAQ: AI Website Builders for SaaS
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Can AI builders actually handle SaaS pricing tables?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Sort of.</strong> Framer handles monthly/annual toggles, tiered pricing, and "recommended" highlights natively. Looks professional, works smoothly. 10Web requires plugins and custom CSS (prepare to fight it). Durable can handle basic tables but falls apart with complex tier structures. For SaaS pricing that converts, Framer is the only one that doesn't feel janky.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Do I really need a demo video on my SaaS landing page?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Yes.</strong> Our test: Adding a 60-second demo video above the fold increased time on site by 73% (1:47 → 3:14) and trial signups by 31%. Screenshot galleries are static. Video demonstrates "how it works" better than any explanation. You don't need production quality—screen recording with voiceover works. Show the product. Build trust. Convert more.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should I use AI-generated copy for my SaaS value prop?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Absolutely not.</strong> AI generates vague garbage like "Transform your data analytics." Our test: Rewrote generic value props to be specific ("Ship 2x faster with automatic task prioritization"). Landing page conversion increased 250% (1.8% → 6.3%). Specific beats vague every time. Write it yourself or hire a copywriter who understands your product. AI copy is conversion poison.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">What's the best way to show social proof for SaaS?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Specific logos, not generic numbers.</strong> "Used by 500+ companies" impresses nobody. "Used by Netflix, Airbnb, Stripe" stops the scroll. Our test: Adding specific client logos increased enterprise leads by 847%. Name-dropping isn't vanity—it's trust. If you don't have recognizable clients yet, use detailed testimonials with metrics. "Saved us 12 hours per week" > "Great tool."
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should I build competitor comparison pages?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
